---
By: Maurice Maeterlinck
Locus:
  Page: 199
  Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Golden Rule
---
Golden Rule You are told you should love your neighbor as yourself; but if
you love yourself measly, childishly, timidly, even so shall you love your
neighbor. Learn therefore to love yourself with a love that is wise and
healthy, that is large and complete.
